    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a very large bowl</p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, 2 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 1/4 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> mustard & shallot dressing</strong></p>",
